{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "b1f0c0de-0001-4a00-9a00-platinumcoin04",
    "name": "PlatinumCoin Pix — Local",
    "description": "Living collection for testing the platform locally, **organized one folder per service**.\n\nIt grows incrementally: every step that adds a public endpoint adds the request here, under its service's folder (convention in CLAUDE.md). Step 48 only finalizes it (pre-request auth, idempotency automation, richer examples).\n\n## How to use\n1. Import this file and `pix-platform.local.postman_environment.json` into Postman; select the **PlatinumCoin Pix — Local** environment.\n2. Run **auth-service → Login (alice)** first — it saves `accessToken` into the environment, so every authenticated request below reuses it automatically.\n3. Base URLs come from `*BaseUrl` env vars (ports mirror `docs/local-dev.md`).\n\nCLI alternative: `newman run tools/postman/pix-platform.postman_collection.json -e tools/postman/pix-platform.local.postman_environment.json`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "auth-service",
      "description": "Identity service — port 8081. Login issues the HS256 JWT that every other service validates. See services/auth-service/README.md.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login (alice)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('accessToken present', () => pm.expect(body.accessToken).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.test('tokenType is Bearer', () => pm.expect(body.tokenType).to.eql('Bearer'));",
                  "// Save the token so every authenticated request in this collection reuses it.",
                  "pm.environment.set('accessToken', body.accessToken);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"alice\",\n  \"password\": \"alice\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{authBaseUrl}}/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{authBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate the seeded user alice (acc-001). On success, saves `accessToken` to the environment."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (bob)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.environment.set('accessToken', pm.response.json().accessToken);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"bob\",\n  \"password\": \"bob\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{authBaseUrl}}/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{authBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticate the seeded user bob (acc-002). Switches `accessToken` to bob's token."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login — bad credentials (401)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('401 Unauthorized', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('problem+json with INVALID_CREDENTIALS', () => {",
                  "  const p = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(p.code).to.eql('INVALID_CREDENTIALS');",
                  "  pm.expect(p.correlationId).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"alice\",\n  \"password\": \"wrong\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{authBaseUrl}}/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{authBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Wrong password ⇒ 401 application/problem+json (no stack trace). Demonstrates the RFC 7807 error contract."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Me (echo principal)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('userId present', () => pm.expect(body.userId).to.be.a('string'));",
                  "pm.test('accountId present', () => pm.expect(body.accountId).to.be.a('string'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{authBaseUrl}}/v1/auth/me",
              "host": ["{{authBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "auth", "me"]
            },
            "description": "Return the caller identity the common-lib JwtAuthFilter derived from the bearer token (`{userId, accountId}`). Run a Login request first so `{{accessToken}}` is set. Without the header it returns 401 problem+json (`code: UNAUTHORIZED`)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{authBaseUrl}}/actuator/health",
              "host": ["{{authBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Actuator health — the contract compose healthchecks rely on. Expect {\"status\":\"UP\"}."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
